WEBVTT

00:02.250 --> 00:04.375
<i>Tonight on st. Elsewhere.</i>

00:04.442 --> 00:08.583
The only reason I ever got
involved with you is because
we had great Sex.

00:10.785 --> 00:13.688
I was puttin' out the fire
when the medication Room
was broken into.

00:13.755 --> 00:17.558
Peter, both you and I know
you have a drug addiction.
I am innocent.

00:17.625 --> 00:22.897
Hey! Cut it out!
You'll kill him!
He's wearing a pacemaker!

00:22.964 --> 00:26.401
So the bum caught me
with a hammer. I still got
my shots in, right?

00:26.467 --> 00:29.670
Aren't you supposed to be
watching Dr. Craig's kid?
Have you seen him?

00:29.737 --> 00:32.406
- Oh, my God. He's dead.
- How's Nina doing?

00:32.473 --> 00:34.642
Seventeen hours
and no change.

00:34.709 --> 00:36.544
Ready? Push.

00:36.611 --> 00:39.447
[ grunting, panting ]

02:20.248 --> 02:22.517
what news of
the maternity ward?
[ Sighs ]

02:22.583 --> 02:26.621
Nina's been in labor for
three hours. She's dilated
only two centimeters.

02:26.688 --> 02:30.758
But she's fine. We're gonna
hang in there with natural
childbirth all the way.

02:30.825 --> 02:34.696
Sorry about bringing you back
down here, but as you can
see, we've been bombarded.

02:34.762 --> 02:37.799
Anything serious?
No. A bus sideswiped
the old state House.

02:37.865 --> 02:41.035
The building's fine.
Mostly Everybody else
is just shook up.

02:41.102 --> 02:44.539
To be honest, I needed to
get out of the labor room
for a little while.

02:44.605 --> 02:46.674
Having a baby
is not easy.

02:46.741 --> 02:50.178
[ chuckles ]
tell that to Nina.
Shirley, you jest.

02:50.244 --> 02:54.315
We got a pool going
on your kid's weight and
the length of Nina's labor.

02:54.382 --> 02:56.551
It's only a buck.
You stand to make a fortune.

02:56.617 --> 03:01.022
Problem is, the only
Spot left is 36 hours,
12 pounds, female.

03:01.089 --> 03:04.559
No, thanks.
You never know. She could be
a female shot-Putter.

03:04.625 --> 03:07.295
Thank you.

04:04.652 --> 04:07.155
â™ªâ™ª [ soft rock ]
Dr. White.

04:07.221 --> 04:10.892
Yeah.
I thought I smelled smoke
coming out of the men's room.

04:10.958 --> 04:13.928
Big deal. Probably
some orderlies
puffing on reefer.

04:13.995 --> 04:16.430
Will you check?

04:16.497 --> 04:19.567
Yeah. What's the matter?
You afraid to go
in there alone, honey?

04:19.634 --> 04:21.601
Oh, come on.

04:24.539 --> 04:27.208
It's in there, Dr. White.

04:27.275 --> 04:29.344
Wait.

04:29.410 --> 04:32.747
Holy-- Call a code red.

04:32.814 --> 04:35.550
John, call
a code red!

05:21.829 --> 05:24.999
Excuse me.
Is there a Mr. Custodi here?

05:26.467 --> 05:28.669
Gene custodi?

05:28.736 --> 05:30.705
[ sighs ]

05:33.574 --> 05:35.476
Mr. Custodi?

05:37.945 --> 05:40.548
How long has he been here?

05:40.615 --> 05:42.583
Gene? Gene?

05:45.453 --> 05:47.388
Oh, man.
What have we got here?

05:47.455 --> 05:50.258
Uh-- Oh, boy.

05:50.324 --> 05:53.695
Give me a hand here, Shirley.
How could you let him
sit here this long?

05:53.761 --> 05:56.164
He was able
to fill out the forms.
He wasn't that out of it.

05:56.230 --> 05:58.166
His pupils
are dilated and equal.

05:58.232 --> 06:00.401
Seconal overdose.
We're gonna
have to lavage him.

06:00.468 --> 06:02.837
[ Daniels ]
Candy, we need you
over here!

06:07.642 --> 06:10.978
Nothing to be alarmed about.
They're probably here
visiting a sick dalmatian.

06:11.045 --> 06:13.348
Why don't you have
a seat.

06:14.615 --> 06:16.918
Mr. Davies?
Yes.

06:16.984 --> 06:19.420
Gratwick Davies?
That's me.

06:19.487 --> 06:21.956
You wanna follow me,
please?

06:27.929 --> 06:30.164
How does it look?
I think we got him in time.

06:30.231 --> 06:32.867
Would you get me
30 C.C.'s Ipecac.

06:32.934 --> 06:35.670
<i>â™ªâ™ª [ one-Man band continues ]</i>

06:41.409 --> 06:46.080
what's his problem?
He's got a few bruised ribs
and he needs a tune-Up.

06:46.147 --> 06:48.049
Good.

06:55.456 --> 06:59.027
Dr. White,
we've got another problem.
What now?

06:59.093 --> 07:03.164
Somebody broke into
the medication room and stole
a whole lot of drugs.

07:03.231 --> 07:05.500
Where?
Down here.

07:09.537 --> 07:12.507
â™ªâ™ª [ Whistling ]

07:13.875 --> 07:16.678
<i>Ehrlich, I want
to talk to you.
I'm sorry.</i>

07:16.744 --> 07:18.780
What for?
I don't know.

07:18.846 --> 07:20.782
It's just
a conditioned response.

07:20.848 --> 07:23.584
You know, dad,
like a Skinner box
or pavlov's dogs.

07:23.651 --> 07:26.454
I know, Steven.
This is my son.
Hi, Steven.

07:26.521 --> 07:29.090
You must be Victor Ehrlich.

07:29.157 --> 07:32.493
Steven is gonna watch me
repair a patent ductus
arteriosus right now.

07:32.560 --> 07:34.495
But after that,
he's all yours.

07:34.562 --> 07:38.299
<i>I expect you to make his
vacation from Med school
as informative as possible.</i>

07:38.366 --> 07:41.636
I want him to get the feel
of what the life
of a resident is all about.

07:41.703 --> 07:43.905
Okay.

07:43.971 --> 07:46.474
After all, he'll be
in your shoes next year.

07:46.541 --> 07:48.910
- Nice bucks.
- Thanks.

07:48.976 --> 07:52.513
Why don't we meet at the Fifth
floor Nurses' station,
oh, say noonish?

07:52.580 --> 07:55.750
- huh?
- Okay, 12:10 on the dot.

07:55.817 --> 08:00.722
I don't want him to
have any special handling
just because he's my son.

08:00.788 --> 08:03.691
Treat him like any other
top student of ohio state.

08:03.758 --> 08:05.727
Yes, sir.

08:10.565 --> 08:12.967
Where's the oxygen,
mahatma?

08:19.006 --> 08:21.843
Good. Son, that'll
clear up your hangover.

08:21.909 --> 08:24.779
Rough night,
Dr. Craig?
Are you kidding?

08:24.846 --> 08:27.882
My son and I were up late
celebrating his homecoming.

08:27.949 --> 08:29.851
Okay, let's get started.

08:32.285 --> 08:36.224
Well, whoever did it
really knew what he
or she was looking for.

08:36.289 --> 08:38.993
What did we lose?
You name it, it's gone.

08:39.059 --> 08:43.231
Enough morphine, diazepam and
seconal to keep the whole city
downed out for a month.

08:43.297 --> 08:44.899
[ sighs ]

08:44.966 --> 08:48.636
I went to the top on this one.
I talked to the commissioner
of police.

08:48.703 --> 08:52.006
He said they're gonna do
everything they can
to try and catch the guy.

08:52.073 --> 08:55.510
I'm no junior g-man,
but it seems pretty obvious
that whoever stole the drugs...

08:55.576 --> 08:58.112
started the fire
as a diversion.
Yeah.

08:58.179 --> 09:01.049
The commissioner asked me
if I thought it
was an inside job.

09:01.115 --> 09:02.984
What did you say?

09:03.051 --> 09:05.119
I said I didn't think so.
What do you really think?

09:05.186 --> 09:08.022
I don't know.
Who was the resident on call?

09:08.089 --> 09:10.825
Peter White.
Oh, boy.

09:14.796 --> 09:16.731
Hi.
Hi.

09:16.798 --> 09:19.067
Hi.
Hi, Nina.

09:19.133 --> 09:23.471
We've still got a ways to go.
I'm gonna do a pelvic exam
After the next contraction.

09:23.538 --> 09:26.441
Why don't you take off
for a while.
No, Thanks.

09:26.507 --> 09:29.944
Honey, you were in
E.R. Until 4:00 a.M.
And then came down here.

09:30.011 --> 09:34.148
Go and get some rest.
Nothing's gonna
happen in the next hour.

09:34.215 --> 09:37.385
She's in good hands.

09:37.452 --> 09:39.787
Okay, I'll be in on call.

09:43.925 --> 09:46.794
How are you feeling?
Great.

09:49.063 --> 09:51.866
Oh, here comes another one.

09:51.933 --> 09:54.902
Okay, now just Relax.
Breathe through it.

09:56.137 --> 09:58.106
That's right.

10:00.041 --> 10:02.010
Very Good.

10:03.344 --> 10:06.914
Mm-Hmm.

10:06.981 --> 10:11.486
<i>[ auschlander ] it was a Monday.
I remember it like it
was yesterday. Cold, dry.</i>

10:11.552 --> 10:14.355
<i>All I wanted to do
was get at the nazis,
so I enlisted.</i>

10:14.422 --> 10:17.458
<i>I didn't let them know
I was a doctor. I wanted
to get in the infantry.</i>

10:17.525 --> 10:20.895
I didn't know there
were any nazis in new guinea.
There weren't.

10:20.962 --> 10:23.531
Roosevelt saw fit to send me
after the japanese.

10:23.598 --> 10:27.135
I guess he knew how much
Macarthur needed me.
It's just as well.

10:27.201 --> 10:30.571
The war in Europe
was a nightmare.
What?

10:30.638 --> 10:32.607
No recurrent malaria,
no beriberi.

10:32.673 --> 10:35.443
All you guys got
was a developed taste
for French wine.

10:35.510 --> 10:38.346
We deserved it after
all that sicilian red
we drank.

10:38.413 --> 10:41.082
I bet you never
thought We'd miss 1943.

10:41.149 --> 10:44.519
No, I guess I never did.

10:44.585 --> 10:47.689
I do miss Rita, though,
all the time.

10:47.755 --> 10:49.691
Well, look at
the bright side.

10:49.757 --> 10:52.193
You're old,
you've got diseases,

10:52.260 --> 10:54.562
you've had heart surgery
and you're wearing a pacemaker.

10:54.629 --> 10:57.165
The way things are going,
you should be with her
very soon.

10:57.231 --> 11:00.902
[ chuckles ]
I don't know whether
that's good news or bad news.

11:00.968 --> 11:03.271
We've come a long way
from Kelly street,
didn't we?

11:03.337 --> 11:05.506
Further than we probably
had any right to.

11:05.573 --> 11:08.142
We didn't end
up in jail like the rest
of the neighborhood.

11:08.209 --> 11:10.678
I guess we fooled
a lot of people.

11:12.480 --> 11:15.850
How did we get
to be so old?

11:15.917 --> 11:18.319
There's nothing wrong
with being old, Danny.

11:18.386 --> 11:21.956
It's just that a lot of people
our age give old a bad name.

11:23.658 --> 11:26.494
Where did the time go?

11:28.329 --> 11:31.799
Which reminds me,
Benny O'Neill died
a couple of months ago.

11:31.866 --> 11:33.801
Of what?

11:33.868 --> 11:36.904
I think it was emphysema
that finally killed him.

11:36.971 --> 11:39.507
I told him a hundred times
to quit smoking.

11:41.776 --> 11:45.713
You know, I like Boston.
Nice town.

11:45.780 --> 11:49.183
I feel the same way.
I couldn't live here Though.

11:49.250 --> 11:51.419
Why not?
I don't know.

11:51.486 --> 11:55.757
There's... too something.

11:58.259 --> 12:00.428
I know what you mean.

12:13.541 --> 12:16.344
Hey, David,
how's it going?

12:17.378 --> 12:20.248
David?

12:20.314 --> 12:23.885
What's the matter with him?
He get up on the wrong side
of Linda this morning?

12:23.951 --> 12:26.721
Dr. Westphall
wants to see you.

12:26.788 --> 12:30.858
My dad told me a lot about you.
Believe me, I'm not
as bad as all that.

12:30.925 --> 12:34.729
No, he admires you.
He sure has a funny
way of showing it.

12:34.796 --> 12:38.032
I know how demanding
he can be. How would you
like to be his son?

12:38.099 --> 12:41.836
They haven't
printed the money yet.
Time to check on a post-Op.

12:41.903 --> 12:44.138
And how are we today,
Marie?

12:44.205 --> 12:48.276
I'm ready to get out of here.
Looks like you're gonna
get your wish.

12:48.343 --> 12:50.478
Would you care to examine
the incision?
Sure.

12:50.545 --> 12:52.580
Who's he?
I didn't mean to be rude.

12:52.647 --> 12:55.950
Dr. Craig, this is Marie.
Marie, Dr. Craig.
Hi.

12:56.017 --> 12:57.985
Just hold it.
Hold it one second.

12:58.052 --> 13:00.621
I have been in this
Dung heap for two weeks...

13:00.688 --> 13:03.291
and Everybody's
been calling me
by my first name--

13:03.358 --> 13:05.560
the doctors, the nurses,
the orderlies.

13:05.626 --> 13:08.162
We try to be friendly
and informal.

13:08.229 --> 13:10.832
It's a one-Way street,
and I'm just sick of it.

13:10.898 --> 13:14.469
I don't know your first name.
I don't even know
if you have one.

13:14.535 --> 13:17.772
It never really
occurred to me.
No, it wouldn't.

13:17.839 --> 13:20.475
You guys are just trained
to be patronizing.

13:20.541 --> 13:22.477
You treat us
all like children.

13:22.543 --> 13:24.746
I'm 54 years old.
I got three kids.

13:24.812 --> 13:28.649
And if one of them dared
to call me Marie,
I'd smack 'em in the head.

13:28.716 --> 13:31.052
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry, Mrs. Benzinger.

13:33.588 --> 13:35.890
[ sighs ]

13:35.957 --> 13:39.527
so much for dazzling you
with my bedside Manner.
Don't worry about it.

13:39.594 --> 13:42.497
My Dad says you just have to
let patients like that
roll off your back.

13:42.563 --> 13:44.766
Yeah. You won't tell him,
will you?

13:44.832 --> 13:47.735
Come on. He's my father.
Do you tell your father
everything?

13:47.802 --> 13:50.938
Not since fourth grade.
You're all right, Steven.

13:51.005 --> 13:55.276
Well, thank you.
It's about lunchtime.
Wanna grab a sandwich?

13:55.343 --> 13:57.578
Uh, no. Uh--

13:57.645 --> 14:00.882
actually, I'd rather
get high.

14:00.948 --> 14:03.184
Excuse me.

14:03.251 --> 14:07.555
Sinsemilla.
Humboldt County--
Blow your head off.

14:07.622 --> 14:09.691
You got a light?

14:15.063 --> 14:17.932
<i>What exactly
are you accusing me of?</i>

14:17.999 --> 14:20.802
I'm not accusing you
of anything. I just want
to know what happened.

14:20.868 --> 14:23.938
I was putting out the fire
when the medication Room
was broken into.

14:24.005 --> 14:28.543
It's all there in my report.
Or didn't you bother to read it?
Sit down.

14:30.978 --> 14:34.749
Dr. Westphall, I'm sorry.
This is a weird time for me.

14:34.816 --> 14:38.353
I know that,
and I appreciate it,

14:38.419 --> 14:40.988
but both you and I know
you have a drug addiction.

14:41.055 --> 14:44.726
I'm doing exactly what you
told me to do. I'm going
to the rehab center.

14:44.792 --> 14:47.729
I'm in the 21-Day program.
Good.

14:47.795 --> 14:50.098
That's good to hear.
I mean it.

14:50.164 --> 14:52.633
But, Peter,
knowing what I know,

14:52.700 --> 14:56.037
I'd be negligent
if I didn't ask you
about last night's break-In.

14:56.104 --> 15:00.007
I am innocent.
I swear it.

15:02.443 --> 15:04.379
Okay, fine.

15:04.445 --> 15:07.648
You believe me?
Just like that?

15:07.715 --> 15:09.684
Yep.

15:15.123 --> 15:17.225
You don't like me
very much, do you?

15:17.291 --> 15:20.328
Peter, I'm well aware
you've had...

15:20.395 --> 15:23.564
more problems this year
than anybody deserves,

15:23.631 --> 15:25.700
but I have to tell you
the truth.

15:25.767 --> 15:29.303
Every time I look at your
evaluation, one thing becomes
more and more clear to me.

15:29.370 --> 15:33.374
<i>You don't seem to be
a very good doctor.</i>

15:33.441 --> 15:36.077
You telling me
you're thinking of dropping me
from the residency program?

15:36.144 --> 15:38.212
It's crossed my mind.

15:45.520 --> 15:48.356
I feel so terrible.
What now?

15:48.423 --> 15:52.026
The pool.
The pool on the length
of Nina Morrison's labor.

15:52.093 --> 15:55.463
I drew 23 hours.
I got 15.

15:55.530 --> 15:58.800
Don't you think it's cruel?
Cruel?

15:58.866 --> 16:01.602
I really hope I win.
I could use the money.

16:01.669 --> 16:06.541
But it's hard to root
for a fellow creature to be
in pain for 23 hours.

16:06.607 --> 16:09.477
Hmm. Hey, guys.
Hello.

16:09.544 --> 16:11.479
Hi, Wayne.
Hi.

16:11.546 --> 16:13.481
What's the count
and the amount?

16:13.548 --> 16:18.186
Nina's been in labor
16 hours, three minutes now.

16:18.252 --> 16:21.356
<i>I never win Anything.
Including the marathon.</i>

16:21.422 --> 16:25.993
Wasn't it exciting, though?
That surging sea of human sweat.

16:26.060 --> 16:29.130
Yeah. Hey, I'm no
Alberto Salazar,

16:29.197 --> 16:32.266
but if I don't get my 10-Mile
running fix in the morning,
I can't get going.

16:32.333 --> 16:35.803
Ten miles a day?
Guys like you are crazy.

16:35.870 --> 16:39.907
You take a healthy
cardiovascular activity
and turn it into an obsession.

16:39.974 --> 16:44.612
- You can't live without it.
- Did you know almost a third
of the people who run...

16:44.679 --> 16:47.148
would rather give up
sex than jogging?

16:47.215 --> 16:49.317
Chandler doesn't
have a choice.

16:49.384 --> 16:53.354
Wayne, could you
pass the salt?
Yeah.

16:53.421 --> 16:56.657
<i>- Look at that tray.
- Yeah, what about it?</i>

16:56.724 --> 16:58.860
Look at the size
of that cake.

16:58.926 --> 17:02.897
I see you squirreling
away those chocolate bars
during rounds.

17:02.964 --> 17:06.733
Okay, so I got a sweet tooth.
Sugar gets me through the day.

17:06.800 --> 17:08.736
Sure beats
not eating at all.

17:08.803 --> 17:11.039
This morning a 14-year-Old
girl came into E.R.

17:11.105 --> 17:13.907
Eighty pounds and
she kept complaining
about how fat she was.

17:13.974 --> 17:16.978
I was reading this university
of arizona research report...

17:17.045 --> 17:21.082
that correlated the behavior
of obsessive runners
with teenage anorexics.

17:21.148 --> 17:26.319
It said they're both bent on
self-Destruction and suggested
they seek psychiatric Help.

17:26.387 --> 17:28.321
Who asked you?

17:28.388 --> 17:32.460
Anybody Who'd quote a university
of arizona research report
is obviously a workaholic.

17:34.062 --> 17:37.031
Speaking of
addictive personalities.

17:37.098 --> 17:40.201
<i>[ Martin ] do you honestly think
he broke into the medication
Room last night?</i>

17:40.268 --> 17:44.439
-He's capable of doing anything.
-Phil, remember--
Innocent until proven guilty.

17:44.505 --> 17:46.541
It really isn't all his fault.

17:46.607 --> 17:50.178
Doctors perpetuate the myth
that drugs are good because
they take the pain away.

17:50.244 --> 17:54.349
We forget the side effects.
Poor Peter.

17:54.415 --> 17:57.485
I'm glad his problem
went public. I was tired
of carrying his load...

17:57.552 --> 17:59.487
and Covering
for his mistakes.

17:59.554 --> 18:02.924
- He makes all of us look bad.
- Anybody want a taste?

18:05.993 --> 18:07.929
[ imitating car revving ]

18:07.995 --> 18:11.599
Whoops. Today's the start
of the st. Eligius 500.

18:11.666 --> 18:14.535
How's Nina doing?
Seventeen hours
and no change.

18:14.602 --> 18:17.538
Oh, well, so much for that.

18:17.605 --> 18:19.574
I'm heading back
down there now.

18:19.640 --> 18:23.277
How's the guy I admitted
last night doing--
the seconal O.D.Er.

18:23.344 --> 18:25.813
Gene custodi?
He's right in There.

18:25.880 --> 18:28.983
His vital signs are stable,
but he was in and out
of it all morning.

18:29.050 --> 18:32.453
Though last time I looked in,
he seemed fairly Responsive.

18:32.520 --> 18:34.489
Think I'll say Hello.
Okay.

18:38.192 --> 18:40.161
Hello, Gene.

18:41.763 --> 18:44.098
I'm Dr. Morrison.
I pumped your stomach
last night.

18:48.669 --> 18:52.040
Well, I just came by
to see how you're doing.

18:52.106 --> 18:55.276
<i>Getting by. You don't
look so good, though.</i>

18:55.343 --> 18:59.013
I'm a little fuzzy.
My Wife's about to have a baby.

18:59.080 --> 19:03.117
Oh, yeah?
I got a kid.

19:03.184 --> 19:06.421
Laurie. She's just
a year old.

19:06.487 --> 19:10.625
Then I don't get it.
How come you're doing
this to yourself?

19:10.692 --> 19:13.461
You mean pop reds?
Yeah.

19:15.296 --> 19:19.767
Look, I got outta high school
about this time last year.

19:19.834 --> 19:22.904
She was pregnant,
so we got married.

19:24.605 --> 19:26.841
And that was fine with me
'cause I really loved her.

19:26.908 --> 19:30.044
Then what
about your responsibility
to your wife and your child?

19:30.111 --> 19:32.547
I don't get to see them.

19:34.449 --> 19:38.019
One night I got home from work
and they were gone.

19:40.421 --> 19:42.390
Not even a note.

19:44.125 --> 19:46.461
Laurie could be dead
for all I know.

19:46.527 --> 19:49.297
You tried to find them?

19:49.364 --> 19:52.033
<i>Till the money ran out.</i>

19:52.100 --> 19:54.969
<i>What about the police?
Oh, man.</i>

19:56.671 --> 20:00.007
Six months is a long time
not to see your kid.

20:00.074 --> 20:03.344
Gene, the pills.
You gotta Stop
punishing yourself.

20:03.411 --> 20:06.481
No, you don't get it at all.

20:06.547 --> 20:12.320
When I take reds and
I'm on the nod, it's like
Laurie's there with me.

20:12.387 --> 20:15.289
Hey, my problem
isn't your problem.

20:15.356 --> 20:18.626
Hello, Jack.
How you doing, Gene?

20:18.693 --> 20:20.628
I see we're gonna
have another talk.

20:20.695 --> 20:23.264
Well, only if you
want to.

20:23.331 --> 20:27.001
It's time I got back down
to the labor room.

20:27.068 --> 20:30.238
You ever been a father before,
Dr. Morrison?

20:30.304 --> 20:32.907
- Nope.
- Today's a big day for you.

20:35.677 --> 20:39.247
The day my daughter was born
was the happiest day of my life.

20:40.481 --> 20:42.417
Good luck.

20:42.483 --> 20:44.452
Thanks.

20:54.662 --> 20:57.832
Have you seen Steven Craig?
No, not since the last time
he was with you.

20:57.899 --> 20:59.534
Thanks.

21:08.576 --> 21:11.913
<i>[ auschlander ] finally,
I succumbed to the pain
and went into a chemo cycle.</i>

21:11.979 --> 21:17.485
<i>- How bad is it?
- Rat poison in
a slow intravenous Drip.</i>

21:17.552 --> 21:21.989
Don't undersell it.
Truly a nauseating
experience.

21:22.056 --> 21:24.258
[ Horn honking ]

21:24.325 --> 21:27.195
What the hell?
That guy Must've
been doing 80.

21:27.261 --> 21:31.065
Rita was killed
by a hit-and-Run driver.
I know.

21:31.132 --> 21:33.134
She would've been 65
this year.

21:36.337 --> 21:38.272
What the hell's
the idea?

21:38.339 --> 21:40.842
I blew the Horn.
Maybe you should turn up
your hearing aid.

21:40.908 --> 21:43.344
You can kill Somebody.
So take it easy.
Herbie, forget it.

21:43.411 --> 21:46.347
Where's your wife?
Out turning tricks
at some old-Age home?

21:46.414 --> 21:49.083
You smart-Mouthed punk.
Herbie, you're
wearing a pacemaker!

21:49.150 --> 21:52.220
Don't answer him.
You're real brave--
a real wiseass.

21:54.188 --> 21:57.692
Okay, it's finished.
You'll have a coronary.
Did you hear what he said?

21:57.759 --> 22:00.595
It was probably
a drugged-Out clown like that
who killed Rita.

22:00.661 --> 22:02.764
Take deep breaths, herbie.

22:02.830 --> 22:05.500
In almost 60 years,
you haven't changed a lot.

22:05.566 --> 22:07.502
We are what we are.

22:07.568 --> 22:11.773
There's an argument for
genetics versus environment.

22:20.148 --> 22:22.784
What the hell's
the idea?

22:22.850 --> 22:26.154
Hey! Cut it out!
You'll kill him!

22:26.220 --> 22:28.956
<i>He's wearing a pacemaker!</i>

22:30.725 --> 22:32.794
Herbie, I'm coming!

22:39.133 --> 22:42.003
You all right, herbie?
Yeah, sure. Let me--

22:43.538 --> 22:45.773
It's over. It's over.

22:50.978 --> 22:53.781
<i>Do you believe that?
Dr. Auschlander,
are you all right?</i>

22:53.848 --> 22:55.983
I've never felt better
in my life.
What happened?

22:56.050 --> 22:57.985
We got into a fight.
What?

22:58.052 --> 23:00.722
You should've been there.
Let's take care
of him first.

23:00.788 --> 23:03.691
Like the old days.
Herbie's not kidding.

23:03.758 --> 23:06.327
Rolling around on
the Hood of that car.

23:06.394 --> 23:09.263
Hold still. I wanna see
where the blood
is coming from.

23:09.330 --> 23:11.232
He's got me pinned.
Can I get some gauze?

23:11.299 --> 23:13.434
He's already grazed me
once with the hammer.

23:13.501 --> 23:17.839
Looks like you're gonna
need some stitches. I'd like
to get a skull series.

23:17.905 --> 23:20.775
I don't think
you're bleeding.
I told you, I'm fine.

23:20.842 --> 23:24.912
Herbie's wearing
a pacemaker.
So?

23:25.947 --> 23:27.882
<i>Dr. Ehrlich?
Call me Victor.</i>

23:27.949 --> 23:31.519
Wait a minute. Aren't you
supposed to be watching
Dr. Craig's kid?

23:31.586 --> 23:33.688
Have you seen him?
In a manner of Speaking.

23:33.755 --> 23:36.991
Wait. Don't tell me.
He got hit by a Gurney,
trapped in an elevator?

23:37.058 --> 23:39.160
What?
Follow me.

23:42.897 --> 23:45.199
Oh, my God. He's Dead.

23:45.266 --> 23:47.935
He's not dead.
He's high.

23:48.002 --> 23:51.539
Again? He smoked a joint
this big this afternoon.

23:51.606 --> 23:54.142
Looks like he's been tapping
into the nitrous oxide.

23:54.208 --> 23:57.078
Kill it, would you, please?

23:57.145 --> 23:59.881
Yo, Steven, up and at 'em.
Come on.

23:59.947 --> 24:02.116
Boy's got a problem.
Help me get him up.

24:02.183 --> 24:04.018
All he needs is some air.

24:04.085 --> 24:07.488
Oh, man, what a rush.

24:09.457 --> 24:11.392
Oh, hi, Victor.
Where you been?

24:11.459 --> 24:13.428
Where I been?
Come on. Wake up.

24:13.494 --> 24:15.430
<i>[ Nina grunting, panting ]</i>

24:15.496 --> 24:19.267
<i>[ Morrison ] you're doing great,
honey. Fifteen more seconds
and you're out of it.</i>

24:19.333 --> 24:21.869
<i>Look at the Monitor.
 Look at the monitor.</i>

24:21.936 --> 24:24.338
<i>[ Nina ]
I don't think I can take
the pain anymore.</i>

24:24.405 --> 24:28.142
<i>Yes, you can. Sure you can.
Can't somebody else
do this for me?</i>

24:28.209 --> 24:31.846
Okay, okay,
we're finished.
We're finished.

24:31.913 --> 24:33.848
Okay, a cleansing breath.

24:33.915 --> 24:35.883
[ Inhales ]

24:37.418 --> 24:40.321
Good.

24:40.388 --> 24:44.659
I think we should talk.
We've been here
for 20 hours now.

24:44.726 --> 24:47.762
You've only dilated
one centimeter in
the last eight hours.

24:47.829 --> 24:50.098
We're still not even close
to delivery.

24:50.164 --> 24:52.100
You think we should
accelerate labor?

24:52.166 --> 24:54.602
We've come this far.
I don't wanna give up.

24:54.669 --> 24:58.806
Nina, we've got a choice.
We can hang in there
another eight hours,

24:58.873 --> 25:01.409
or we can speed things along
with a shot of pitocin.

25:01.476 --> 25:03.444
<i>I don't wanna do that.</i>

25:03.511 --> 25:07.815
I know I can make it.
I know you can too.

25:07.882 --> 25:11.552
But if we hold out
too much longer, it could
potentially harm the baby.

25:11.619 --> 25:15.656
But, Jack, what about
all the time we put in--
all the classes and preparation?

25:15.723 --> 25:19.594
It's not wasted.
It got us this far, didn't it?

25:19.660 --> 25:22.096
You're doing great.

25:22.163 --> 25:24.966
But the fact is,
we're here to have a baby.

25:25.033 --> 25:28.870
And whether we do it naturally
or not, at this point
it's secondary, right?

25:30.805 --> 25:32.774
Right.

25:36.878 --> 25:40.548
Start an I.V. With
pitocin in it. Let's get
the delivery room Ready.

25:44.552 --> 25:48.022
One of your doctors told me
my heart's running
like a swiss watch.

25:48.089 --> 25:50.024
He also tell you
you got a punctured eardrum?

25:50.091 --> 25:53.327
Yeah, and that's too bad.
It was my good ear.

25:53.394 --> 25:56.931
I called Tony.
I told him what happened.
I wish you hadn't done that.

25:56.998 --> 26:00.835
He's having enough problems
with his deliveries showing up
late from korea.

26:00.902 --> 26:02.837
I'll drive you back
to the hotel.

26:02.904 --> 26:05.406
A Lesser man Would've had
to spend the night here
at club Med.

26:05.473 --> 26:08.176
A smarter man
wouldn't have gotten
into that foray.

26:08.242 --> 26:12.714
I haven't felt so good
in 25 years. I don't give
a damn about my ear.

26:12.780 --> 26:16.284
So the bum caught me
with a hammer. I still got
my shots in, right?

26:16.351 --> 26:18.453
I know what you mean!

26:18.519 --> 26:22.757
You know, for a second there--
for a split second
of a moment,

26:22.824 --> 26:25.727
I was 18 again and immortal.

26:25.793 --> 26:29.364
I know. I could feel
the adrenaline exploding
out of my heart too.

26:29.430 --> 26:32.066
By the way, thanks.
For what?

26:32.133 --> 26:35.436
For being there.

26:35.503 --> 26:38.473
Danny, I'm gonna
tell you a secret.

26:40.641 --> 26:43.177
We're gonna live Forever.

26:53.755 --> 26:55.690
Hi.
Good luck.

26:55.757 --> 26:57.692
Thanks.

26:57.759 --> 26:59.794
Hi. This isn't
the time to visit.

26:59.861 --> 27:01.829
It should be over in
a couple hours.

27:01.896 --> 27:06.401
I'll put this in her room,
so she'll have it
when she comes out. Good luck.

27:09.070 --> 27:11.005
Finally.
Yeah.

27:11.072 --> 27:14.108
How you doing?
Pretty Good.
Is Peter on call?

27:14.175 --> 27:16.177
I don't know.
Let's go check.
Okay.

27:16.244 --> 27:18.179
How's it going
between you and him?

27:18.246 --> 27:21.049
It's not. I haven't seen him
since his birthday.

27:21.115 --> 27:23.051
I know what
you're going through.

27:23.117 --> 27:27.488
My first Husband didn't want me
to go out with the girls.
He wanted to go out with them.

27:27.555 --> 27:30.758
That's Peter.
My second Husband
didn't want me to work.

27:30.825 --> 27:33.127
The problem was, he didn't
want to work either.

27:33.194 --> 27:37.031
My third husband, well,
that's better left unsaid.

27:37.098 --> 27:39.400
I can't imagine going
through any of this
more than once.

27:39.467 --> 27:42.870
Me either.
You know, Myra,

27:42.937 --> 27:47.141
an interesting thing
happened to me because
of my mastectomy.

27:47.208 --> 27:51.546
I learned you don't throw
relationships away like you
would broken appliances.

27:51.612 --> 27:55.283
You fix them.
You make them work.

27:55.350 --> 27:58.486
I wish it was that easy.
Maybe it is.

27:58.553 --> 28:02.423
I think what you've got to do
is figure out what you
really need in life...

28:02.490 --> 28:04.759
and what you're
willing to do for it.

28:06.828 --> 28:08.796
Thank you, Helen.

28:12.934 --> 28:14.869
Hi, Victor.
Hi.

28:14.936 --> 28:16.871
May I?
Yeah.

28:16.938 --> 28:20.375
Want some?
Alphabet soup.
Mm-Mm, Good.

28:20.441 --> 28:23.811
No, I'm not in the mood.
Bummed out?

28:23.878 --> 28:26.347
No, no, no.

28:26.414 --> 28:29.417
V.J., you're a man
of the world.
Let me ask you a question.

28:29.484 --> 28:32.186
I have this friend--
my friend's boss has a son...

28:32.253 --> 28:35.523
Who my friend's boss asked
my friend to baby-Sit at work.

28:35.590 --> 28:37.925
Are you with me so far?
No.

28:37.992 --> 28:40.528
You sure you don't
want some soup?
No, thank you.

28:40.595 --> 28:43.531
Anyway, the point is
that the boss's son
is doing something...

28:43.598 --> 28:46.267
that the friend knows
the boss wouldn't like,

28:46.334 --> 28:50.004
and my friend
who likes the Boss's son
and respects the boss,

28:50.071 --> 28:52.407
can't figure out what to do.

28:52.473 --> 28:55.276
You mean, Dr. Craig's son,
Steven, is taking drugs?

28:55.343 --> 28:57.311
Yes!

28:58.379 --> 29:00.581
You really are
in a Pickle.

29:00.648 --> 29:03.785
Well, okay.
You have any age-Old indian
wisdom you wanna share with me?

29:03.851 --> 29:07.889
In my family,
we have an old proverb--

29:07.955 --> 29:10.425
"When you open your window
for fresh air,

29:10.491 --> 29:13.695
you're bound to find
a locust in your Curry."

29:13.761 --> 29:16.564
I see. Okay.

29:16.631 --> 29:20.068
Look, I am
an anesthesiologist.

29:20.134 --> 29:25.339
My job is to knock people out
when they are operated on
so they don't feel the pain.

29:25.406 --> 29:28.009
That's a good thing.

29:28.076 --> 29:32.280
But when this gift
is abused,
all it causes is pain.

29:32.347 --> 29:36.884
So, you're saying I should be
a stoolie, squeal on the kid
and tell Craig everything.

29:36.951 --> 29:39.787
No.

29:39.854 --> 29:44.192
I have been working
under Dr. Craig for
a while and a half now.

29:44.258 --> 29:47.829
We don't have
what you may call
a meaningful relationship.

29:47.895 --> 29:49.831
But I think I know him
well enough to tell...

29:49.897 --> 29:53.234
that the son's abuse will
break the father's heart.

29:53.301 --> 29:57.105
Aha. So, you're saying
I shouldn't talk to Craig.

29:57.171 --> 29:59.407
No.
Then what are you saying?

29:59.474 --> 30:01.442
Talk to the son.

30:02.877 --> 30:04.846
[ moans ]

30:06.381 --> 30:10.018
<i>I'm not dealing, I swear.
Who you talking to?</i>

30:10.084 --> 30:13.021
Not even a pharmacist walks
around the streets with that
many pills on them.

30:13.087 --> 30:16.224
I told you, I'm not dealing.
Let me see
your prescription.

30:16.290 --> 30:19.060
Please.
Listen up, Gene.

30:19.127 --> 30:21.396
With the stuff we found,
you've had it,

30:21.462 --> 30:23.498
unless you wanna tell me
who your connection is.

30:23.564 --> 30:27.168
Gimme a break.
I tell you that
and I'm a dead man.

30:27.235 --> 30:30.872
Listen, Buddy boy,
you're a dead man Anyway.

30:30.938 --> 30:33.841
Your record isn't exactly
spotless when it comes
to drug abuse.

30:33.908 --> 30:38.546
This time, no probation.

30:38.613 --> 30:41.883
The state has
an old-Fashioned way of
rehabilitating guys like you--

30:41.949 --> 30:44.752
cold turkey
in a prison cell.

30:45.953 --> 30:47.922
Have a nice day.

30:53.194 --> 30:55.163
Can you get away
for a couple of hours?

30:55.229 --> 30:58.132
If you don't spend some time
with me, I'm not sure
what's gonna happen.

30:58.199 --> 31:02.003
This week alone, I've already
taken off two days
to be with you.

31:02.070 --> 31:06.107
I have my career
to think about.
You're not being fair.

31:06.174 --> 31:09.077
Just for an hour or so.
Come on.

31:09.143 --> 31:11.412
I feel like I'm slipping
and I need some Help.

31:11.479 --> 31:14.148
That's why you're
at rehab.
I walked outta that place.

31:14.215 --> 31:17.618
I couldn't stand it. All those
people talking about--
You really don't want any help.

31:17.685 --> 31:21.923
You wanna just complain--
Please, don't start
on me like that.

31:21.989 --> 31:25.893
The last thing
I wanna hear right now is
what a jerk you think I am.

31:25.960 --> 31:29.297
<i>I'm the best thing
that ever happened to you.
You said so yourself.</i>

31:29.364 --> 31:32.500
I never said that.
You got me confused me with
your wife or someone else.

31:32.567 --> 31:35.903
- Jill, please.
- Living with you is
no picnic, Peter.

31:35.970 --> 31:38.373
- You've wrecked my car.
- The insurance covered that.

31:38.439 --> 31:42.710
- You're constantly borrowing
money that you never pay back.
- What is it with you?

31:42.777 --> 31:45.546
I'm dying in here
and you're still kicking.

31:45.613 --> 31:47.548
Come back.

31:47.615 --> 31:51.719
The only reason I ever
got involved with you
is because we had great Sex.

31:51.786 --> 31:56.991
But ever since you started
going heavy on the drugs,
you're damaged goods.

31:57.058 --> 31:59.794
You're all the same.

31:59.861 --> 32:04.932
It took you no time to move in,
Peter. It's gonna even
take you less to move out.

33:22.210 --> 33:24.112
<i>[ Clattering ]</i>

33:36.057 --> 33:37.859
hello?

33:37.925 --> 33:40.328
Are you okay in there?

33:42.430 --> 33:44.732
[ Screaming ]

33:44.799 --> 33:47.802
[ grunting, panting ]

33:50.538 --> 33:52.940
the Baby's head's
about to show.

33:53.007 --> 33:54.942
Now, Nina, I want you
to listen to me.

33:55.009 --> 33:58.112
You're gonna feel a burning
sensation when the Baby's
head being born.

33:58.179 --> 34:00.715
Don't let that scare you.

34:00.782 --> 34:03.451
Ready? Push.

34:04.952 --> 34:09.223
<i>You're doing great.
Very Good. Again.</i>

34:09.290 --> 34:11.492
Real good, honey.
Very Good.

34:11.559 --> 34:14.362
Jack, look.
You can see the Baby's hair.

34:16.330 --> 34:18.366
[ Chuckles ]
[ sobbing ]

34:18.433 --> 34:22.070
I'm gonna do an episiotomy.
Now don't push through
this next contraction.

34:22.136 --> 34:26.139
Nina, I'm gonna make
a small incision to enlarge
the opening so you don't tear.

34:26.206 --> 34:28.909
<i>- Do it. Do it.
- Here we go.</i>

34:28.976 --> 34:31.946
<i>Small Pushes.
That's good, honey.
Very good.</i>

34:32.013 --> 34:35.248
I got it. I got it.

34:35.315 --> 34:38.518
[ Laughs ]
that was quick.

34:38.585 --> 34:43.358
[ panting ]
what is it?
What is it?

34:43.424 --> 34:45.860
It's a boy.

34:48.362 --> 34:50.398
And the time is 6:33.

34:50.465 --> 34:53.434
It's a boy, Jack.

34:53.501 --> 34:55.469
It's a boy!

34:57.605 --> 35:00.608
<i>[ Thunderclap ]</i>

35:02.977 --> 35:05.213
is doc fujiyama here?

35:05.279 --> 35:07.348
No, he went
to the health club.

35:07.415 --> 35:10.084
He was supposed
to have the results
on the neilsen autopsy.

35:10.151 --> 35:13.287
Oh, the man who died
sitting with his family
watching television?

35:13.354 --> 35:15.957
Yeah.

35:16.024 --> 35:18.292
Here it is.
Thanks.

35:19.927 --> 35:21.996
This is incomplete.
Why, Wayne?

35:22.063 --> 35:24.932
There's no indication of
what show he was watching.

35:24.999 --> 35:27.135
[ chuckles ]
my guess is Cable.

35:27.201 --> 35:29.670
They play all the really
good movies on Cable.

35:29.737 --> 35:34.776
I love lying in bed, watching.
There are no... Interruptions.

35:34.842 --> 35:38.913
Uh-Huh.
Uh, well, Bye, cath.

35:38.980 --> 35:40.915
Wayne, wait.

35:40.982 --> 35:43.051
<i>[ thunderclap ]</i>

35:43.117 --> 35:45.720
<i>Have you ever seen
the French Lieutenant's woman?</i>

35:45.787 --> 35:49.157
It's on tonight.
I saw it.

35:49.223 --> 35:53.895
Can you ever forget
the look on Meryl's face when
she was standing on the quay,

35:53.961 --> 35:59.167
a lone figure on
a windswept cob,
waiting for her man to return?

35:59.233 --> 36:04.305
Then she turned and Jeremy
saw her for the first time.

36:04.372 --> 36:07.075
<i>[ thunderclap ]</i>

36:11.913 --> 36:16.050
Well, uh, what happened
with you and
Warren Applegate?

36:16.117 --> 36:18.052
It's finished.
Oh.

36:18.119 --> 36:20.588
He was just a passing fancy.

36:20.655 --> 36:23.725
Wayne, can I be Frank?
You can be
anybody you want.

36:23.791 --> 36:27.795
Please, I want to bare
my soul to you.

36:27.862 --> 36:31.466
I saw the way you were looking
at me in the cafeteria.

36:31.532 --> 36:33.801
Like you used to, before.

36:33.868 --> 36:37.538
Oh, damn it, Wayne!
Ever Since that night when I
walked out of your apartment--

36:37.605 --> 36:41.809
Cathy, you are
not interested in me.
You are just obsessed with Sex.

36:41.876 --> 36:45.013
Yes.

36:45.079 --> 36:49.283
Yes, I am. But only
with you, Wayne.

36:50.618 --> 36:52.920
You're better than Tony...

36:52.987 --> 36:55.189
and David...

36:55.256 --> 36:57.492
and Scott...

36:57.558 --> 37:00.194
and Steve.
Steve.

37:00.261 --> 37:02.230
Even Gary.
Gary.

37:03.364 --> 37:07.168
I still wear your heart
close to mine.

37:07.235 --> 37:10.071
Well, look, Cathy,
I gotta go.
Please, don't.

37:10.138 --> 37:12.673
No, you don't understand.
I am in the middle...

37:12.740 --> 37:15.376
of the beginning of
a very nice relationship
with Shirley Daniels.

37:15.443 --> 37:18.413
Anything that might happen
between us right now
will screw that up.

37:18.479 --> 37:20.682
And I don't
wanna screw that up.
Shh.

37:20.748 --> 37:23.051
No, Cathy. No, Cathy.
Wayne, shh.

37:23.117 --> 37:25.086
Cathy--
Close your eyes.

37:25.153 --> 37:29.090
Cathy--
[ muttering ]

37:30.925 --> 37:32.860
remember?

37:32.927 --> 37:37.832
"A day will come when you
shall be called to account
for what you have done to me."

37:49.077 --> 37:52.113
I knew
you'd come back.

37:54.782 --> 37:57.819
<i>Was it our stuff?
[ Beale ]
a syringe.</i>

37:57.885 --> 38:00.755
<i>My guess is retrieved
from a garbage pail.</i>

38:00.822 --> 38:05.059
Custodi's chart didn't mention
he was into heavy stuff.
He wasn't.

38:05.126 --> 38:08.196
Then what did he use?
Nothing.

38:08.262 --> 38:12.400
He took the empty syringe
and shot up an air bubble.

38:12.467 --> 38:15.470
Instant heart attack.

38:15.536 --> 38:17.505
He left this note.

38:18.940 --> 38:20.875
<i>[ woman over P.A. ]
attention, Everybody.</i>

38:20.942 --> 38:24.379
<i>Jack and Nina Morrison
are the proud parents
of a seven-Pound baby boy.</i>

38:24.445 --> 38:27.548
<i>Length of LABOR:
22 hours, 12 minutes.</i>

38:29.217 --> 38:31.819
<i>[ knocking ]
come in.</i>

38:33.388 --> 38:36.324
Oh, hiya, Victor.
Care to join me?

38:36.391 --> 38:38.993
Uppers. Help you sail right
through the evening carnage.

38:39.060 --> 38:42.196
I used to take 'em
for philosophy exams.
They gave me divine guidance.

38:42.263 --> 38:44.532
Are you nuts?
Your father could walk in here.

38:44.599 --> 38:46.734
He said he'd be back
in three minutes.

38:46.801 --> 38:50.505
When my Dad says three minutes,
he means three minutes.

38:50.571 --> 38:53.908
Get your feet off there.

38:53.975 --> 38:56.544
Victor, what's the problem?
I sense hostility here.

38:56.611 --> 39:00.982
I don't get it.
You're bright, good-Looking,
with an incredible future.

39:01.049 --> 39:05.153
Sky's the limit.
I'm no saint. I grew up in
california in the '60s.

39:05.219 --> 39:08.256
So I understand
what you're doing here.

39:08.322 --> 39:12.794
But I learned the human body
can only take so much and
then brain cells start to fry.

39:12.860 --> 39:14.796
I got it under control.

39:14.862 --> 39:19.434
Go on up to the psych ward and
talk to some of the junkies
and speed freaks...

39:19.500 --> 39:21.703
and the acid casualties
up there.

39:21.769 --> 39:24.205
They don't know who they are,
but they have it
under control too.

39:24.272 --> 39:27.475
If I closed my eyes,
I could swear my dad
was in the room.

39:27.542 --> 39:32.747
What you're doing here shows
so much disrespect for a man who
obviously loves you very much.

39:32.814 --> 39:34.749
I think that's
what bothers me the most.

39:34.816 --> 39:39.187
I've got nothing against my Dad.
I'm just leading my own life.

39:39.253 --> 39:41.522
Oh, yeah?
Suppose I tell him.

39:41.589 --> 39:43.524
So, tell him.

39:45.693 --> 39:49.163
Hi, Dad.
Steven, Ehrlich.

39:49.230 --> 39:52.467
Steven and I are going
to the party for Jack Morrison.

39:52.533 --> 39:55.770
Care to join us?
Thank you, sir.

39:55.837 --> 39:58.172
- How are you two getting along?
- Terrific.

39:58.239 --> 40:01.409
Yeah, great.
Okay, let's go.

40:54.862 --> 40:57.832
[ crying ]

41:03.805 --> 41:05.773
Peter?

41:07.809 --> 41:10.078
I saw you in the hallway.

41:13.681 --> 41:18.419
Nina and Jack had a boy.
That's Good.
Jack wanted a boy.

41:19.954 --> 41:23.191
They're throwing a party
in the fourth floor
Doctors' Lounge.

41:24.726 --> 41:29.097
Yeah, all my friends
will be there.
What do you mean?

41:29.163 --> 41:33.401
I mean, Myra,
I'm hated around here.

41:33.468 --> 41:35.670
They don't hate you.

41:35.737 --> 41:37.705
I don't hate you.

41:38.940 --> 41:41.442
Well, you should.

41:41.509 --> 41:44.579
I've given you
reason enough to.

41:44.645 --> 41:48.316
Well, believe me,
I've done my share
of hurting you too.

41:48.383 --> 41:50.885
I don't even
remember anymore.

41:54.022 --> 41:57.125
Did we ever
love each other?

41:57.191 --> 41:59.160
Yes.

42:01.562 --> 42:03.998
Then how did
we get here?

42:05.533 --> 42:07.502
I don't know.

42:16.477 --> 42:19.347
Remember when you asked me
to marry you?

42:21.449 --> 42:24.419
We knew for a long time
that we wanted to get married,

42:24.485 --> 42:29.691
but neither of us wanted to be
the first one to say it.

42:29.757 --> 42:31.726
But you asked me...

42:33.828 --> 42:37.165
on that spring day
when we were walking
the quad at brown.

42:37.231 --> 42:40.168
[ crying ]

42:40.234 --> 42:44.272
and when the words came out,
I started to cry because...

42:44.338 --> 42:48.543
that's all I ever wanted
was to be your wife
and have your children.

42:51.312 --> 42:53.748
I loved you that much.

42:55.850 --> 42:57.785
[ Sniffles ]

42:57.852 --> 43:00.555
[ sighs ]
I miss providence.

43:00.621 --> 43:02.990
Yeah, me too.

43:08.229 --> 43:10.198
Come home.

43:20.441 --> 43:23.411
<i>[ thunderclap ]</i>

43:25.880 --> 43:29.684
it's happened three times
this month. We're not
gonna catch him. I know it.

43:29.751 --> 43:32.153
Mind if I have one?
Not at all. Go ahead.

43:32.220 --> 43:35.323
How 'bout you?
No.

43:35.390 --> 43:40.094
Suppose for now, we consolidate
the medication rooms by putting
them on every other floor?

43:40.161 --> 43:42.130
Sure.

43:44.399 --> 43:48.836
We could double security,
but either way, it's gonna
cause a lot of aggravation.

43:52.607 --> 43:55.476
We can talk about
this later if you like.

43:55.543 --> 43:58.913
Am I that distracted?
Yeah.

43:58.980 --> 44:01.115
Anything I can do?
Make me young.

44:01.182 --> 44:03.484
Yeah, wish I could.

44:04.952 --> 44:07.355
This afternoon
when I was thrashing
around with herbie--

44:07.422 --> 44:09.724
It's lucky the two of you
weren't killed.

44:09.791 --> 44:13.227
It'd been years
since I felt that vital.

44:13.294 --> 44:17.832
I realized what a mistake
I've made trying to grow old
gracefully.

44:17.899 --> 44:20.501
"Rage, rage, against
the dying of the light."

44:20.568 --> 44:24.739
Why shouldn't we?
Because, my friend,
it's a waste of time.

44:24.806 --> 44:28.876
But, Donald, won't you
at least admit you'd give up
everything you've worked for,

44:28.943 --> 44:32.980
learned, achieved,
to feel the way you were at 18?

44:33.047 --> 44:35.783
Of course.
But if we did,
where would that leave us?

44:35.850 --> 44:37.952
Confused, selfish,
immature.

44:38.019 --> 44:40.488
I, for one, wouldn't want
to go through that again.

44:40.555 --> 44:43.424
Well, I would, in a second.

44:43.491 --> 44:45.827
<i>[ thunderclap ]</i>

44:45.893 --> 44:49.464
Oh, Jack and Nina
Morrison had a baby boy
a little while ago.

44:49.530 --> 44:53.401
There's gonna be a party
on the fourth floor.

44:53.468 --> 44:55.703
Well, then, rather than dwell
on what's gone forever,

44:55.770 --> 44:59.073
perhaps it would be Wiser
to look to the future.

